cards.question: What is compact (cortical) bone
cards.answer: a hard layer that is dense, strong, and durable. It makes up around 80% of adult bone mass

cards.question: What are three main cell types involved in the bone maintenance process
Where could bone marrow be found
cards.answer: bone marrow is found in almost all bones where cancellous bone is present

cards.question: Out of what main parts the nervous system consists
cards.answer: brain, spinal cord, sensory organs, and all of the nerves that connect these organs with the rest of the body
